- Oh, gosh. All right.

243
00:07:59,519 --> 00:08:00,678
- Go ahead, Young Ok.
- That was gross.

244
00:08:00,679 --> 00:08:03,148
I pick Yeong Cheol.

245
00:08:03,149 --> 00:08:04,589
(Young Ok chose Yeong Cheol.)

246
00:08:04,689 --> 00:08:06,018
And I have my reason.

247
00:08:06,019 --> 00:08:07,088
- What's the reason?
- Because he's pitiful.

248
00:08:07,089 --> 00:08:08,089
Because he's pitiful?

249
00:08:09,189 --> 00:08:11,388
- He transcends generations.
- Everyone else...

250
00:08:11,389 --> 00:08:13,128
- Everyone sees him as pitiful.
- We have similar names.

251
00:08:13,129 --> 00:08:15,768
Jang Hoon has marriage experience, at least.

252
00:08:15,769 --> 00:08:17,528
- Ho Dong is married now.
- That's right.

253
00:08:17,529 --> 00:08:19,298
Sang Min is on his second marriage.

254
00:08:19,299 --> 00:08:20,868
- So he always smiles happily.
- She knows everything.

255
00:08:20,869 --> 00:08:22,408
- Only I've been single all my life.
- He's never gotten married.

256
00:08:22,409 --> 00:08:23,538
- I didn't realize that.
- Oh, right.

257
00:08:23,539 --> 00:08:26,078
- There's someone I've always liked.
- That's why he's pitiful.

258
00:08:26,079 --> 00:08:27,079
Who is it?

259
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:28,948
I've liked him for a long time.

260
00:08:28,949 --> 00:08:29,949
- What?
- Really?

261
00:08:29,950 --> 00:08:33,019
It's Ho Dong, who transformed from a ssireum player to a comedian.

262
00:08:34,049 --> 00:08:35,848
- Here's why I like him.
- All right.

263
00:08:35,849 --> 00:08:38,688
There are two top stars who I knew would become successful.

264
00:08:38,689 --> 00:08:39,988
- Who are they?
- They are...

265
00:08:39,989 --> 00:08:41,689
One of them is Actor Won Bin.

266
00:08:42,689 --> 00:08:43,859
The other is Ho Dong.

267
00:08:44,429 --> 00:08:46,728
- Both succeeded. I was right.
- They're different from each other.

268
00:08:46,729 --> 00:08:48,098
- You have a keen eye.
- Yes.

269
00:08:48,099 --> 00:08:50,528
Won Bin and I are so different from each other.

270
00:08:50,529 --> 00:08:52,068
Indeed. I liked you as a comedian,

271
00:08:52,069 --> 00:08:53,799
and I liked him as an actor.

272
00:08:54,339 --> 00:08:57,438
- She has a keen eye, right?
- I have a question.

273
00:08:57,439 --> 00:09:00,039
Have the three of you always been close?

274
00:09:00,509 --> 00:09:01,509
No.

275
00:09:02,809 --> 00:09:05,648
- Hang on. You're not close?
- We thought you were close.

276
00:09:05,649 --> 00:09:08,118
- I'm close to her.
- You two are close?

277
00:09:08,119 --> 00:09:09,848
- You're close to Neung Mi.
- We've always been close.

278
00:09:09,849 --> 00:09:11,588
And it took me and Mi Ja a while to become friends.

279
00:09:11,589 --> 00:09:14,658
We didn't really have a chance to see each other.

280
00:09:14,659 --> 00:09:16,428
- So we weren't very close.
- They worked at different networks.

281
00:09:16,429 --> 00:09:17,988
But we've known each other since we were young.

282
00:09:17,989 --> 00:09:19,498
Oh, because you worked at different networks?

283
00:09:19,499 --> 00:09:22,468
It's not like the three of us are best friends or anything.

284
00:09:22,469 --> 00:09:24,099
Then... Hold on a second.

285
00:09:24,669 --> 00:09:25,738
- We thought...
- Then...

286
00:09:25,739 --> 00:09:27,268
- We thought you were very close, - Exactly.

287
00:09:27,269 --> 00:09:28,269
- Right.
- and that's why you came here...

288
00:09:28,270 --> 00:09:29,908
- all together.
- We thought you were best friends.

289
00:09:29,909 --> 00:09:32,408
- How did you all gather together?
- Exactly.

290
00:09:32,409 --> 00:09:35,438
It's not like we planned to get together.

291
00:09:35,439 --> 00:09:38,879
I thought about who would suit the theme of the show,

292
00:09:39,119 --> 00:09:43,048
and I realized all three of us would be fitting for being goofy here.

293
00:09:43,049 --> 00:09:44,519
I came here because Young Ok asked me to.

294
00:09:45,719 --> 00:09:46,958
That's such an honest answer.

295
00:09:46,959 --> 00:09:47,988
- Neung Mi.
- That's true.

296
00:09:47,989 --> 00:09:49,729
- Can you make me spicy fish stew?
- I asked her to come here with me.

297
00:09:51,189 --> 00:09:52,898
You punk, eat it at your own house.

298
00:09:52,899 --> 00:09:55,028
- That's our Iron Foul Mouth.
- "You punk."

299
00:09:55,029 --> 00:09:56,069
(Neung Mi's honesty drew Gye In back.)

300
00:09:57,069 --> 00:09:58,969
Why do you keep asking her to make you spicy fish stew?

301
00:09:59,039 --> 00:10:00,899
You can make it by yourself, Gye In.

302
00:10:01,199 --> 00:10:03,269
My wife makes only chicken soup.

303
00:10:05,209 --> 00:10:06,979
- She makes only chicken soup.
- That explains why.

304
00:10:07,509 --> 00:10:09,078
- Gosh. Seriously.
- My goodness.

305
00:10:09,079 --> 00:10:11,179
- By the way, I'm sorry, - Yes?

306
00:10:11,349 --> 00:10:14,779
but even though you've come back after graduation,

307
00:10:15,019 --> 00:10:16,348
we have a procedure to follow.

308
00:10:16,349 --> 00:10:17,548
- That's right.
- Of course.

309
00:10:17,549 --> 00:10:22,059
Young Ok, if you brought something, bring it to me.

310
00:10:23,159 --> 00:10:24,858
- Soo Geun, act as you always do.
- What I brought...

311
00:10:24,859 --> 00:10:27,059
- Go and receive it, you brat.
- Hold on.

312
00:10:27,129 --> 00:10:28,729
- Why?
- You rude brat.

313
00:10:28,829 --> 00:10:29,829
"You rude brat?"

314
00:10:29,830 --> 00:10:32,599
I mean, look at this little punk.

315
00:10:32,999 --> 00:10:36,268
If you need it, you should come and collect it yourself.

316
00:10:36,269 --> 00:10:38,068
- But this school has...
- Must I bring it to you?

317
00:10:38,069 --> 00:10:39,478
- its own rules and procedures.
- You punk.

318
00:10:39,479 --> 00:10:41,308
- That's how it works here.
- Are you getting smart with us?

319
00:10:41,309 --> 00:10:43,749
Whoever comes here...

320
00:10:43,949 --> 00:10:46,779
Even Mr. Shin Gu came to me to bring it to me.

321
00:10:47,249 --> 00:10:48,918
- But we're different.
- Shin Gu...

322
00:10:48,919 --> 00:10:50,148
may have brought it to you,

323
00:10:50,149 --> 00:10:51,388
- but we have to stay seated.
- It's hard for us.

324
00:10:51,389 --> 00:10:53,319
- We can't move around.
- We can't.

325
00:10:53,859 --> 00:10:55,119
They said it at the same time.

326
00:10:55,829 --> 00:10:57,788
- They said it at the same time.
- They said it at the same time.

327
00:10:57,789 --> 00:10:58,959
- "We can't."
- "We can't."

328
00:10:59,529 --> 00:11:01,898
The transfer form to Men on a Mission.

329
00:11:01,899 --> 00:11:05,838
Names, Kim Young Ok, Sa Mi Ja, and Nam Neung Mi!

330
00:11:05,839 --> 00:11:08,569
(Names: Nam Neung Mi, Kim Young Ok, Sa Mi Ja)

331
00:11:09,409 --> 00:11:12,808
- They wrote down their birthplaces.
- Their birthplaces?

332
00:11:12,809 --> 00:11:14,238
- Their birthplaces?
- First,

333
00:11:14,239 --> 00:11:16,909
- Me?
- Young Ok and Mi Ja...

334
00:11:17,109 --> 00:11:19,618
were born in Gyeongseong-bu, Gyeonggi Province.

335
00:11:19,619 --> 00:11:20,878
- Gyeongseong-bu?
- Where is Gyeongseong-bu?

336
00:11:20,879 --> 00:11:23,288
- The place from "The Wild Days?"
- "The Wild Days?"

337
00:11:23,289 --> 00:11:24,948
- Gyeongseong-bu...
- Like the Gyeongseong Empire?

338
00:11:24,949 --> 00:11:26,418
- You see, I was born...
- What?

339
00:11:26,419 --> 00:11:30,189
- in the Japanese colonial era.
- That's where Seoul is today.

340
00:11:30,459 --> 00:11:32,598
- Which means, I was born in Seoul.
- Seoul.

341
00:11:32,599 --> 00:11:34,699
Specifically, I was born in Seodaemun-gu.

342
00:11:34,999 --> 00:11:37,069
- The area is now part of Jongno-gu.
- I see.

343
00:11:37,199 --> 00:11:39,969
I was born in Hongpa-dong. Let me summarize for you.

344
00:11:40,199 --> 00:11:43,139
My family has been rooted in Hongpa-dong for five generations.

345
00:11:43,339 --> 00:11:45,268
- I was born and raised in Seoul.
- Oh, my.

346
00:11:45,269 --> 00:11:46,638
You know the real people portrayed...

347
00:11:46,639 --> 00:11:48,008
- in "The Wild Days," right?
- Of course.

348
00:11:48,009 --> 00:11:51,108
- Including Goo Ma Juk.
- Have you ever met any of them?

349
00:11:51,109 --> 00:11:52,109
- Yes.
- Well...

350
00:11:52,449 --> 00:11:55,549
And as for me, I was also...

351
00:11:55,789 --> 00:11:58,888
- born in Seoul.
- She was born in "Seoul."

352
00:11:58,889 --> 00:12:00,688
- I was born in Naengcheon-dong, - I see.

353
00:12:00,689 --> 00:12:01,789
Seodaemun-gu, Seoul.

354
00:12:02,089 --> 00:12:03,789
- Naengcheon-dong?
- That's where I was born.

355
00:12:03,989 --> 00:12:06,598
- You two are from the same area.
- That's right.

356
00:12:06,599 --> 00:12:09,669
- We were born in the same area.
- Although we're not so close now,

357
00:12:09,869 --> 00:12:12,369
we met each other when we were young.

358
00:12:13,069 --> 00:12:15,268
- Really?
- Her brother was a theater actor.

359
00:12:15,269 --> 00:12:16,808
I had already started my career as a theater actress...

360
00:12:16,809 --> 00:12:19,939
since I'm older than Mi Ja.

361
00:12:20,239 --> 00:12:21,508
I saw her back then,

362
00:12:21,509 --> 00:12:23,749
- and she was very pretty.
- Right.

363
00:12:24,149 --> 00:12:28,649
- Have you ever ridden a streetcar?
- Of course.

364
00:12:28,719 --> 00:12:30,048
- When we were little, - Yes.

365
00:12:30,049 --> 00:12:31,989
- streetcars were all we had...
- They were all we had...

366
00:12:32,049 --> 00:12:34,389
- for public transportation.
- Right. Or taxis.

367
00:12:34,459 --> 00:12:36,089
We took a streetcar to school too.

368
00:12:36,259 --> 00:12:39,659
Until we got married and our kids were about six,

369
00:12:39,829 --> 00:12:40,898
- there were streetcars.
- You see...

370
00:12:40,899 --> 00:12:43,598
How did you pay the fare? Cash?

371
00:12:43,599 --> 00:12:44,768
How much was the fare?

372
00:12:44,769 --> 00:12:46,538
- Wasn't the currency "hwan?"
- Maybe people used tokens.

373
00:12:46,539 --> 00:12:47,838
I don't remember that.

374
00:12:47,839 --> 00:12:50,209
- We used tokens back in the day.
- Oh, you used tokens.

375
00:12:50,339 --> 00:12:52,069
- Something like bus tickets.
- Exactly.

376
00:12:52,209 --> 00:12:55,779
We used paper tickets and would tear one off to pay the fare.

377
00:12:56,009 --> 00:12:59,419
You must have witnessed the Liberation Day...

378
00:12:59,549 --> 00:13:01,249
with your very own eyes.

379
00:13:01,349 --> 00:13:02,518
- The Liberation Day?
- Yes.

380
00:13:02,519 --> 00:13:03,789
I saw exactly what happened that day.

381
00:13:04,249 --> 00:13:08,488
I remember adults pouring into the streets and cheering.

382
00:13:08,489 --> 00:13:10,859
I cheered along without knowing what it meant. I was only eight.

383
00:13:11,229 --> 00:13:13,958
- I just cheered as they did.
- That's natural as she was eight.

384
00:13:13,959 --> 00:13:15,158
- People were all excited that...
- I can remember that day.

385
00:13:15,159 --> 00:13:16,328
the country was liberated.

386
00:13:16,329 --> 00:13:18,829
- Do you still remember it vividly?
- That memory is still vivid.

387
00:13:19,569 --> 00:13:21,598
There was this song that played. It goes like this.

388
00:13:21,599 --> 00:13:26,378
(Taegeukgi flutters on the liberated stagecoach)

389
00:13:26,379 --> 00:13:27,479
- It goes like this.
- Oh, my.

390
00:13:28,479 --> 00:13:29,848
(The two seniors are excited, talking about the liberation.)

391
00:13:29,849 --> 00:13:30,948
Is it not over yet?

392
00:13:30,949 --> 00:13:33,249
(The two seniors are excited, talking about the liberation.)

393
00:13:33,319 --> 00:13:34,418
Gosh, I'm bored.

394
00:13:34,419 --> 00:13:36,419
(Gosh, I'm bored!)

395
00:13:37,019 --> 00:13:38,019
(Generation gap, born in 1946, 1937, 1940)

396
00:13:38,020 --> 00:13:39,919
- Neung Mi is so funny.
- She's the youngest among them.

397
00:13:40,019 --> 00:13:41,959
- How old were you, Neung Mi?
- On the Liberation Day?

398
00:13:42,019 --> 00:13:43,628
- She wasn't even born.
- I wasn't even in my mom's womb.

399
00:13:43,629 --> 00:13:46,329
- Neung Mi, are you from Seoul?
- After the liberation.

400
00:13:46,699 --> 00:13:50,098
Neung Mi was born in Cheongyang-gun, South Chungcheong Province.

401
00:13:50,099 --> 00:13:51,268
The area that we know...

402
00:13:51,269 --> 00:13:52,899
Did you wear straw shoes?

403
00:13:53,099 --> 00:13:54,438
I think I wore rubber shoes.

404
00:13:54,439 --> 00:13:55,538
- Oh, rubber shoes?
- Yes.

405
00:13:55,539 --> 00:13:56,709
Black rubber shoes.

406
00:13:56,839 --> 00:13:58,538
- Black rubber shoes.
- Black rubber shoes?

407
00:13:58,539 --> 00:14:00,008
- Did you walk...
- They were black.

408
00:14:00,009 --> 00:14:02,749
Hearing she's from Cheongyang...

409
00:14:03,179 --> 00:14:05,748
takes me back to when my family fled there during the war...

410
00:14:05,749 --> 00:14:07,249
when I was nine years old.

411
00:14:09,189 --> 00:14:10,248
- Nice.
- When you fled during the war?

412
00:14:10,249 --> 00:14:11,548
- Everything connects.
- The story...

413
00:14:11,549 --> 00:14:14,359
- I see the connection between them.
- I see why they're here together.

414
00:14:14,559 --> 00:14:16,428
- This itself is a piece of history.
- Exactly.

415
00:14:16,429 --> 00:14:19,428
- Korean modern history.
- I was 14...

416
00:14:19,429 --> 00:14:20,628
when my family sought refuge during the war.

417
00:14:20,629 --> 00:14:21,759
We...

418
00:14:22,299 --> 00:14:23,898
- We just...
- Here's how we went there.

419
00:14:23,899 --> 00:14:24,968
We just headed south...

420
00:14:24,969 --> 00:14:26,799
- to get away from Seoul.
- You kept going south?

421
00:14:26,939 --> 00:14:28,868
In the early days of the Korean War,

422
00:14:28,869 --> 00:14:30,808
- we weren't able to flee.
- We weren't able to flee.

423
00:14:30,809 --> 00:14:32,838
- People said...
- Not in the early days of the war.

424
00:14:32,839 --> 00:14:34,879
the commies would catch you.

425
00:14:35,079 --> 00:14:36,908
- During the Third Battle of Seoul, - During the Third Battle of Seoul,

426
00:14:36,909 --> 00:14:39,378
- people fled...
- my father said we should leave.

427
00:14:39,379 --> 00:14:40,778
We heard all these scary rumors,

428
00:14:40,779 --> 00:14:42,179
like how Chinese army was coming down.

429
00:14:42,549 --> 00:14:45,188
Word was that they'd tear people apart. Everyone was terrified.

430
00:14:45,189 --> 00:14:47,959
She's telling everything I was going to tell.

431
00:14:48,859 --> 00:14:50,989
- This is why they don't jibe.
- Why did you do that?

432
00:14:51,089 --> 00:14:53,358
- That's why they're not close.
- Why did you tell all that story?

433
00:14:53,359 --> 00:14:54,928
Her story ends when she gets to Cheongyang.

434
00:14:54,929 --> 00:14:56,128
- What else is there to be told?
- But maybe she wanted to tell that.

435
00:14:56,129 --> 00:14:58,069
- Change the subject. I'm bored.
- She wanted to say...

436
00:14:58,329 --> 00:14:59,468
No.

437
00:14:59,469 --> 00:15:01,469
- Right.
- Mi Ja, has your story ended?

438
00:15:01,539 --> 00:15:03,608
- So we...
- What happened in Cheongyang?

439
00:15:03,609 --> 00:15:04,938
We all carried huge bundles of belongings...

440
00:15:04,939 --> 00:15:06,278
- on our backs...
- Really?

441
00:15:06,279 --> 00:15:08,178
- and fled south.
- Yes.

442
00:15:08,179 --> 00:15:09,678
- I have...
- She carried it on her back.

443
00:15:09,679 --> 00:15:11,378
- two older brothers.
- You have two brothers.

444
00:15:11,379 --> 00:15:15,179
Including my parents, there were five of us fleeing together.

445
00:15:15,549 --> 00:15:16,818
- But there was no place to stay.
- Right.

446
00:15:16,819 --> 00:15:18,348
So we had to knock on random doors...

447
00:15:18,349 --> 00:15:21,189
- and beg for a room for a night.
- You begged for a room.

448
00:15:21,319 --> 00:15:23,188
When we were rejected, my father begged again.

449
00:15:23,189 --> 00:15:27,158
"Young man, it's too cold outside for my little girl here."

450
00:15:27,159 --> 00:15:28,629
He begged for a room again.

451
00:15:28,729 --> 00:15:30,928
That young man said yes.

452
00:15:30,929 --> 00:15:32,639
And we stayed there...

453
00:15:32,939 --> 00:15:36,309
until Seoul was reclaimed. We stayed in Cheongyang.

454
00:15:36,409 --> 00:15:37,839
We owe him and his family a lot.

455
00:15:37,909 --> 00:15:41,679
- Next, we'll find out...
- It happened during the war.

456
00:15:41,979 --> 00:15:43,678
- when our guests debuted.
- Right. When did they debut?

457
00:15:43,679 --> 00:15:44,878
- Right.
- Right now, we...

458
00:15:44,879 --> 00:15:46,848
People will be surprised when they hear it.

459
00:15:46,849 --> 00:15:48,818
- Why?
- First, Young Ok made her debut...

460
00:15:48,819 --> 00:15:50,818
- Yes?
- in 1959...

461
00:15:50,819 --> 00:15:53,188
as an announcer at KBS Chuncheon Broadcasting Corporation.

462
00:15:53,189 --> 00:15:55,288
- She was an announcer?
- She debuted as an announcer first.

463
00:15:55,289 --> 00:15:57,488
Before I became an announcer,

464
00:15:57,489 --> 00:16:00,059
- I worked at HLKZ-TV.
- HLKZ-TV?

465
00:16:00,199 --> 00:16:02,698
I worked as an actress for quite some time.

466
00:16:02,699 --> 00:16:04,198
- To launch...
- HLKZ-TV?

467
00:16:04,199 --> 00:16:05,668
television broadcasting in Korea,

468
00:16:05,669 --> 00:16:09,509
Hankook Ilbo and RCA formed a partnership.

469
00:16:09,839 --> 00:16:13,308
There were only 8,000 televisions in Korea back then.

470
00:16:13,309 --> 00:16:15,639
They were doing live broadcasts.

471
00:16:16,009 --> 00:16:18,579
But the project came to a halt because the building caught fire.

472
00:16:19,179 --> 00:16:21,819
I needed a job to make ends meet.

473
00:16:22,049 --> 00:16:24,789
I was willing to take any job to earn a living.

474
00:16:24,889 --> 00:16:27,318
That's when I was hired by KBS Chuncheon Broadcasting Corporation.

475
00:16:27,319 --> 00:16:28,488
- As an announcer.
- As an announcer.

476
00:16:28,489 --> 00:16:30,059
- I have a question.
- Go ahead.

477
00:16:30,129 --> 00:16:32,528
Since you were an announcer back in the day,

478
00:16:32,529 --> 00:16:34,028
I wonder if you remember...

479
00:16:34,029 --> 00:16:36,899
- some of the comments on the news.
- Of course, I remember.

480
00:16:36,999 --> 00:16:39,499
Here is the news for today.

481
00:16:39,739 --> 00:16:41,668
HLKZ-TV.

482
00:16:41,669 --> 00:16:44,809
After the opening comment like this, I'll read the news stories.

483
00:16:45,639 --> 00:16:49,139
- But from what I've gathered, - That's... Yes?

484
00:16:49,479 --> 00:16:51,979
Young Ok left her job as an announcer...

485
00:16:52,079 --> 00:16:54,148
and became a voice actress.

486
00:16:54,149 --> 00:16:55,418
- What happened?
- I had my reasons.

487
00:16:55,419 --> 00:16:56,988
I worked as an announcer only for eight months.

488
00:16:56,989 --> 00:16:59,389
- As an announcer?
- I was paid two dollars a month.

489
00:16:59,659 --> 00:17:02,658
Back then, the rent for a shabby house...

490
00:17:02,659 --> 00:17:04,059
up on the hill was 30 cents.

491
00:17:04,259 --> 00:17:06,399
- And I needed food too.
- She lived in such a house?

492
00:17:06,559 --> 00:17:08,558
My rent and food expenses took up almost my entire salary.

493
00:17:08,559 --> 00:17:10,898
- Your finances were out of balance.
- I thought long and hard...

494
00:17:10,899 --> 00:17:12,468
before quitting my job and moving to Seoul.

495
00:17:12,469 --> 00:17:15,638
But the best decision I've ever made was...

496
00:17:15,639 --> 00:17:17,709
- doing the voice actress audition.
- Oh, I see.

497
00:17:18,069 --> 00:17:20,939
- I became a voice actress.
- What kind of roles did you play?

498
00:17:21,009 --> 00:17:23,509
- You wouldn't even know her works.
- Sorry? What roles?

499
00:17:24,879 --> 00:17:26,918
There's something that we all must know.

500
00:17:26,919 --> 00:17:29,279
- In "Robot Taekwon V,"
- "Robot Taekwon V." That's right.

501
00:17:29,449 --> 00:17:32,388
- she voiced Hoon.
- But he's the male lead.

502
00:17:32,389 --> 00:17:33,518
- The lead character?
- Really?

503
00:17:33,519 --> 00:17:35,559
I voiced that character when I was 40.

504
00:17:35,659 --> 00:17:36,958
- I mean, Hoon.
- When you were 40?

505
00:17:36,959 --> 00:17:37,989
Really?

506
00:17:39,559 --> 00:17:43,129
(This is Young Ok's voice.)

507
00:17:43,469 --> 00:17:45,328
- The voice of Hoon is...
- Hoon from "Robot Taekwon V." Yes.

508
00:17:45,329 --> 00:17:46,398
your voice?

509
00:17:46,399 --> 00:17:48,398
I've already told this story before.

510
00:17:48,399 --> 00:17:50,609
- Don't act like you're surprised.
- Right.

511
00:17:51,039 --> 00:17:52,978
- This is our 1st time hearing that.
- This is my 1st time hearing that.

512
00:17:52,979 --> 00:17:54,038
- They really didn't know that.
- Right.

513
00:17:54,039 --> 00:17:56,648
- I didn't know that either.
- I never knew...

514
00:17:56,649 --> 00:17:58,309
- Young Ok voiced Hoon.
- Me neither.

515
00:17:58,479 --> 00:17:59,479
- I also voiced Kouji Kabuto...
- Did you know that?

516
00:17:59,480 --> 00:18:00,918
- in "Mazinger Z."
- No.

517
00:18:00,919 --> 00:18:01,919
- Kouji Kabuto too?
- Kouji Kabuto?

518
00:18:01,920 --> 00:18:02,948
I'm often asked to do the voice,

519
00:18:02,949 --> 00:18:05,348
but my voice would sound just as old as I look now.

520
00:18:05,349 --> 00:18:06,618
My voice wouldn't sound like a young boy's.

521
00:18:06,619 --> 00:18:07,959
- I'm sure it would.
- Here's my famous line.

522
00:18:08,219 --> 00:18:10,258
"Mazinger!"

523
00:18:10,259 --> 00:18:12,188
- The character from "Mazinger Z?"
- She still sounds the same.

524
00:18:12,189 --> 00:18:15,029
Many voice actors overdo it when voicing a kid.

525
00:18:15,299 --> 00:18:18,299
"Hey, did you do that?" Those who overdid it like this...

526
00:18:18,569 --> 00:18:20,039
rarely got their moment to shine.

527
00:18:20,369 --> 00:18:21,598
- I didn't overdo it.
- Right.

528
00:18:21,599 --> 00:18:24,109
"Did you do that? Ho Dong, come out."

529
00:18:24,209 --> 00:18:25,638
"Do you want to play with me?"

530
00:18:25,639 --> 00:18:27,138
I tried to keep it natural,

531
00:18:27,139 --> 00:18:30,048
and my voice sounded like a little boy's.

532
00:18:30,049 --> 00:18:32,408
- I'm sorry, but Neung Mi...
- Neung Mi...

533
00:18:32,409 --> 00:18:34,548
- You should fight it.
- "Mister, can you help my dad?"

534
00:18:34,549 --> 00:18:37,119
- I'm sleepy.
- To make myself sound like a man...

535
00:18:37,249 --> 00:18:38,649
How about we have a sip of coffee?

536
00:18:39,389 --> 00:18:41,189
- Whose coffee is this?
- Go ahead. Drop the honorifics.

537
00:18:41,289 --> 00:18:43,358
- Young Ok, whose coffee is this?
- "Young Ok."

538
00:18:43,359 --> 00:18:44,659
My gosh. That's mine.

539
00:18:45,389 --> 00:18:46,559
I'm sorry.

540
00:18:46,759 --> 00:18:47,829
- She's upset.
- Right.

541
00:18:47,929 --> 00:18:49,259
(Sipping)

542
00:18:49,969 --> 00:18:51,099
I'm sorry.

543
00:18:51,469 --> 00:18:53,499
- She just had a sip...
- "That's mine."

544
00:18:53,769 --> 00:18:54,969
- Who's next?
- "That's mine."

545
00:18:55,139 --> 00:18:56,468
- Mi Ja...
- "Mi Ja?"

546
00:18:56,469 --> 00:18:58,908
- Mi Ja made her debut...
- Is it my turn?

547
00:18:58,909 --> 00:18:59,978
- Yes.
- Yes.

548
00:18:59,979 --> 00:19:02,508
She made her debut in 1963... As Young Ok told us earlier,

549
00:19:02,509 --> 00:19:05,409
she was among the first batch of voice actors at DBS.

550
00:19:06,479 --> 00:19:08,148
Voice acting was more popular...

551
00:19:08,149 --> 00:19:10,248
- than screen acting back then.
- That's true.

552
00:19:10,249 --> 00:19:12,718
Back then, only 1 or 2 households in the entire neighborhood...

553
00:19:12,719 --> 00:19:14,719
- owned a television.
- That's right.

554
00:19:14,789 --> 00:19:18,058
- So, radio prevailed.
- She was a voice actress too.

555
00:19:18,059 --> 00:19:20,358
And voice actors worked hard...

556
00:19:20,359 --> 00:19:22,969
to land a role in a radio drama.

557
00:19:23,099 --> 00:19:27,439
In 1963, I went to DBS for an audition.

558
00:19:27,799 --> 00:19:30,138
The waiting line wound around several times...

559
00:19:30,139 --> 00:19:33,439
and stretched all the way to Mugyo-dong.

560
00:19:33,709 --> 00:19:35,608
- There were many applicants.
- For the audition?

561
00:19:35,609 --> 00:19:37,509
At the time,

562
00:19:37,809 --> 00:19:39,579
I already had a child.

563
00:19:40,349 --> 00:19:42,119
- What's important is...
- Yes?

564
00:19:42,279 --> 00:19:44,118
that they hired only single women.

565
00:19:44,119 --> 00:19:46,049
Did you hide the fact that you were married?

566
00:19:46,159 --> 00:19:47,588
In the job posting, it was written like,

567
00:19:47,589 --> 00:19:48,618
(Exclusive Voice Actor Auditions)

568
00:19:48,619 --> 00:19:51,828
"Limited to unmarried men and women."

569
00:19:51,829 --> 00:19:54,099
- Really?
- But I missed that.

570
00:19:54,199 --> 00:19:55,258
- You did?
- I would've ignored it...

571
00:19:55,259 --> 00:19:56,298
- even if I had seen it.
- Of course.

572
00:19:56,299 --> 00:19:58,329
So I took the audition.

573
00:19:58,399 --> 00:20:01,368
Rumor has it that Jeon Won Ju almost got you...

574
00:20:01,369 --> 00:20:02,768
- fired.
- Bringing her name up is enough...

575
00:20:02,769 --> 00:20:04,409
- to fill me with rage.
- Why?

576
00:20:05,109 --> 00:20:07,438
- How come?
- I might get fired again.

577
00:20:07,439 --> 00:20:08,638
- Right.
- I get filled with rage.

578
00:20:08,639 --> 00:20:10,249
What was it that almost got you fired?

579
00:20:10,779 --> 00:20:11,878
I had to hide the fact that...

580
00:20:11,879 --> 00:20:12,979
- I had a child.
- Right.

581
00:20:13,349 --> 00:20:15,948
But my mom brought my child to the office...

582
00:20:15,949 --> 00:20:18,149
- so that I could breastfeed him.
- I see.

583
00:20:18,389 --> 00:20:21,858
- But my child wouldn't eat.
- Oh, no.

584
00:20:21,859 --> 00:20:24,429
- You were in a rush.
- "Please eat, dear baby."

585
00:20:24,559 --> 00:20:26,598
"If you take your time, someone might come in,"

586
00:20:26,599 --> 00:20:27,858
"and I might get busted."

587
00:20:27,859 --> 00:20:29,828
She came in at that very moment.

588
00:20:29,829 --> 00:20:30,868
- She saw it.
- Jeon Won Ju?

589
00:20:30,869 --> 00:20:32,228
- Ms. Jeon Won Ju?
- Yes.

590
00:20:32,229 --> 00:20:34,739
There's no need for the honorifics. Anyway, she came in.

591
00:20:35,069 --> 00:20:36,339
- I was surprised, - Right.

592
00:20:37,339 --> 00:20:39,008
- and so was she.
- I see.

593
00:20:39,009 --> 00:20:40,708
She thought I was a maiden, but I had a baby in my arms...

594
00:20:40,709 --> 00:20:43,079
- and was breastfeeding him.
- You turned out to be a mom.

595
00:20:43,579 --> 00:20:45,078
She left the room and shouted,

596
00:20:45,079 --> 00:20:48,519
"Guys, Mi Ja is breastfeeding a baby in here!"

597
00:20:50,089 --> 00:20:51,249
My gosh.

598
00:20:51,489 --> 00:20:54,019
You almost got fired. That was really close.

599
00:20:54,119 --> 00:20:55,688
Loud enough for Mi Ja to hear?

600
00:20:55,689 --> 00:20:57,628
- As soon as she left.
- As soon as she left.

601
00:20:57,629 --> 00:20:58,928
- Did you get fired?
- What happened next?

602
00:20:58,929 --> 00:21:01,259
When I was tearing up,

603
00:21:01,329 --> 00:21:03,798
the producer called me over.

604
00:21:03,799 --> 00:21:04,828
(The producer called for her.)

605
00:21:04,829 --> 00:21:07,169
- She got busted.
- "Come here, Sa Mi Ja!"

606
00:21:07,699 --> 00:21:10,569
I greeted him with my baby in my arms.

607
00:21:11,609 --> 00:21:12,839
"Good gracious."

608
00:21:14,179 --> 00:21:17,679
"Come to the 10am rehearsal tomorrow."

609
00:21:17,779 --> 00:21:18,808
(The producer turned a blind eye to her marital status.)

610
00:21:18,809 --> 00:21:20,048
She could've really gotten fired.

611
00:21:20,049 --> 00:21:21,749
Who's the older one?

612
00:21:22,179 --> 00:21:23,388
Is it Jeon Won Ju?

613
00:21:23,389 --> 00:21:26,419
Jeon Won Ju is a year or two older than me. Right?

614
00:21:26,659 --> 00:21:28,558
Actually, right, Young Ok?

615
00:21:28,559 --> 00:21:30,388
(Right, Young Ok?)

616
00:21:30,389 --> 00:21:31,888
She wanted to call her by her name.

617
00:21:31,889 --> 00:21:33,558
(Getting used to not using honorifics)

618
00:21:33,559 --> 00:21:35,298
"Right, Young Ok?"

619
00:21:35,299 --> 00:21:36,728
Did you make up with Jeon Won Ju...

620
00:21:36,729 --> 00:21:38,169
- after that?
- Right.

621
00:21:39,129 --> 00:21:41,138
We didn't make up.

622
00:21:41,139 --> 00:21:43,139
- What?
- Even if we were in the same drama,

623
00:21:43,439 --> 00:21:45,508
I'd always be sitting at the head...

624
00:21:45,509 --> 00:21:47,209
- of the room.
- She was always a madam.

625
00:21:47,379 --> 00:21:49,679
Meanwhile, Won Ju was in an apron,

626
00:21:50,279 --> 00:21:52,678
- made a feast, - Right.

627
00:21:52,679 --> 00:21:54,619
- served it in brass dishes, - Yes.

628
00:21:54,779 --> 00:21:57,388
and carried it over to me.

629
00:21:57,389 --> 00:21:59,489
- Imagine how heavy it must've been.
- Right.

630
00:21:59,959 --> 00:22:03,089
"Madam, I'm here with your meal."

631
00:22:04,259 --> 00:22:05,888
I'd tell her to come in.

632
00:22:05,889 --> 00:22:07,759
- She was carrying the heavy table.
- Right.

633
00:22:08,159 --> 00:22:09,768
What a great revenge.

634
00:22:09,769 --> 00:22:12,199
- Yes, the greatest revenge.
- She put the table down.

635
00:22:12,469 --> 00:22:13,898
I couldn't help but laugh.

636
00:22:13,899 --> 00:22:15,168
And so?

637
00:22:15,169 --> 00:22:16,339
And I did laugh.

638
00:22:16,769 --> 00:22:19,269
"Why'd you have to laugh?"

639
00:22:19,369 --> 00:22:21,339
- "Why'd you laugh?"
- "You try carrying it. It's heavy."

640
00:22:21,779 --> 00:22:23,809
I said, "Serve it again to me."

641
00:22:25,449 --> 00:22:26,848
- You got your revenge.
- Good riddance.

642
00:22:26,849 --> 00:22:28,618
- A real revenge.
- What a revenge.

643
00:22:28,619 --> 00:22:30,088
- The best revenge.
- Yes, the best.

644
00:22:30,089 --> 00:22:31,848
- Making a mistake.
- Yes, the best revenge.

645
00:22:31,849 --> 00:22:34,488
You get along with Won Ju now, right?

646
00:22:34,489 --> 00:22:35,918
With how old we are now,

647
00:22:35,919 --> 00:22:37,359
- we're no enemies.
- Right.

648
00:22:37,429 --> 00:22:38,458
- She and I are...
- Listen.

649
00:22:38,459 --> 00:22:39,859
As for Neung Mi...

650
00:22:40,199 --> 00:22:42,029
- In 1967, - Gosh.

651
00:22:42,359 --> 00:22:43,769
she was KBS's sixth recruit.

652
00:22:43,969 --> 00:22:45,968
Does the sixth recruit mean as a TV actress?

653
00:22:45,969 --> 00:22:47,598
- Correct.
- Sixth open recruitment.

654
00:22:47,599 --> 00:22:49,438
What's a bigger shock is that...

655
00:22:49,439 --> 00:22:51,468
- Five more recruits.
- there's also the fifth recruit.

656
00:22:51,469 --> 00:22:52,809
Who was the first recruit?

657
00:22:52,909 --> 00:22:54,508
- First recruit...
- I don't remember...

658
00:22:54,509 --> 00:22:55,678
many of the first recruits,

659
00:22:55,679 --> 00:22:57,678
but there was the late Kim Nan Yeong.

660
00:22:57,679 --> 00:22:59,078
I can only recall her.

661
00:22:59,079 --> 00:23:00,378
Were you active in the same year as Kang Bu Ja?

662
00:23:00,379 --> 00:23:02,078
- Yes.
- We were on different TV stations.

663
00:23:02,079 --> 00:23:04,119
- So the TV stations were different.
- I was in KBS.

664
00:23:04,289 --> 00:23:06,189
- She was also KBS.
- Who was?

665
00:23:06,889 --> 00:23:07,889
- Kang Bu Ja.
- Kang Bu Ja.

666
00:23:07,890 --> 00:23:09,059
- Really, Mi Ja?
- Yes.

667
00:23:09,319 --> 00:23:11,189
- "Really?"
- "Really, Mi Ja?"

668
00:23:11,289 --> 00:23:13,359
- That's right.
- She turned out to be your senior.

669
00:23:13,459 --> 00:23:14,528
Same recruits...

670
00:23:14,529 --> 00:23:16,098
Neung Mi thought she was in a different TV station,

671
00:23:16,099 --> 00:23:17,298
- but they were in the same station.
- You were both KBS.

672
00:23:17,299 --> 00:23:19,268
They didn't bump into each other. Who was recruited with you?

673
00:23:19,269 --> 00:23:20,498
- About the colleagues...
- Who are your colleagues?

674
00:23:20,499 --> 00:23:21,838
None of the sixth recruits is active.

675
00:23:21,839 --> 00:23:22,969
But there are two senior...

676
00:23:23,069 --> 00:23:25,008
- special recruits.
- Special recruits?

677
00:23:25,009 --> 00:23:27,479
- Who?
- Choi Bul Am and Shin Gu.

678
00:23:27,809 --> 00:23:29,949
The only open recruit left is me.

679
00:23:30,009 --> 00:23:31,009
Oh, my.

680
00:23:31,010 --> 00:23:34,349
Did you always dream of becoming an actress?

681
00:23:34,719 --> 00:23:36,648
No. If I had had money...

682
00:23:36,649 --> 00:23:38,489
and had attended school,

683
00:23:38,749 --> 00:23:41,888
I would have wanted to become a teacher or a judge.

684
00:23:41,889 --> 00:23:44,389
- These were my childhood dreams.
- Gosh, what big dreams.

685
00:23:44,589 --> 00:23:46,428
But since I didn't have money and voice artists...

686
00:23:46,429 --> 00:23:48,028
- were trending back then, - Right.

687
00:23:48,029 --> 00:23:49,558
I decided to take the voice artist auditions.

688
00:23:49,559 --> 00:23:51,969
But before the auditions, I attended an academy.

689
00:23:52,399 --> 00:23:54,299
The director of the academy told me,

690
00:23:54,639 --> 00:23:56,608
"I know a play actor."

691
00:23:56,609 --> 00:23:59,709
"I recommended you, so give it a shot."

692
00:23:59,979 --> 00:24:02,438
I took part in it, and that very first work received...

693
00:24:02,439 --> 00:24:03,808
the Presidential Award.

694
00:24:03,809 --> 00:24:04,878
Oh, my.

695
00:24:04,879 --> 00:24:06,448
- Your first work got you the award?
- Yes.

696
00:24:06,449 --> 00:24:08,179
- Your first work as an actress?
- Yes.

697
00:24:08,479 --> 00:24:10,148
- Amazing.
- You followed that path and...

698
00:24:10,149 --> 00:24:11,618
- You immediately rose to fame.
- Correct.

699
00:24:11,619 --> 00:24:12,619
- Right.
- Yes.

700
00:24:12,620 --> 00:24:15,659
- What about Mi Ja?
- A director...

701
00:24:15,689 --> 00:24:17,429
was told...

702
00:24:17,759 --> 00:24:20,558
to look for me in DBS...

703
00:24:20,559 --> 00:24:22,328
for a new role.

704
00:24:22,329 --> 00:24:23,469
He dropped by.

705
00:24:23,569 --> 00:24:25,098
I've always liked acting more than being...

706
00:24:25,099 --> 00:24:27,768
- a voice actress.
- So you liked acting more.

707
00:24:27,769 --> 00:24:28,869
I agreed to transfer.

708
00:24:29,169 --> 00:24:31,939
The news that I was transferring to TBC became public.

709
00:24:32,339 --> 00:24:35,509
I began acting in a drama at TBC,

710
00:24:36,179 --> 00:24:38,609
and it totally suited me.

711
00:24:39,049 --> 00:24:40,118
It was your calling.

712
00:24:40,119 --> 00:24:42,179
- "This is my way."
- My way.

713
00:24:42,879 --> 00:24:46,089
Then it's been a while since you came to TBC, or JTBC now.

714
00:24:47,189 --> 00:24:48,288
Is that so, sir?

715
00:24:48,289 --> 00:24:50,289
- Yes.
- I see.

716
00:24:50,359 --> 00:24:52,488
- We agreed to drop the formality.
- Here...

717
00:24:52,489 --> 00:24:54,198
You've come here after a long time.

718
00:24:54,199 --> 00:24:55,798
- Cuss at him.
- It feels like...

719
00:24:55,799 --> 00:24:57,298
I'm back in my parents' place.

720
00:24:57,299 --> 00:25:00,198
I actually didn't have a dream.

721
00:25:00,199 --> 00:25:01,669
I simply wanted...

722
00:25:01,699 --> 00:25:04,269
to get married...

723
00:25:04,369 --> 00:25:06,438
- to a fine, rich man...
- A good wife?

724
00:25:06,439 --> 00:25:08,378
and be a housewife.

725
00:25:08,379 --> 00:25:11,608
Though I wasn't good at it, I liked singing,

726
00:25:11,609 --> 00:25:13,179
so I was in the choir.

727
00:25:13,349 --> 00:25:15,049
But it was my Korean language teacher.

728
00:25:15,319 --> 00:25:18,248
To recommend acting, he came to the choir...

729
00:25:18,249 --> 00:25:19,788
and called me out to chat.

730
00:25:19,789 --> 00:25:21,858
- "Since you're good at Korean,"
- An excellent student.

731
00:25:21,859 --> 00:25:24,458
"you'll do well in acting."

732
00:25:24,459 --> 00:25:26,088
With that,

733
00:25:26,089 --> 00:25:27,598
when I was in the third year of middle school,

734
00:25:27,599 --> 00:25:30,099
- I acted in a work called...
- "A Little Princess."

735
00:25:30,129 --> 00:25:31,598
"A Little Princess."

736
00:25:31,599 --> 00:25:33,469
That was...

737
00:25:33,739 --> 00:25:36,708
the turning point of my life.

738
00:25:36,709 --> 00:25:38,208
- It started then.
- Strangely enough,

739
00:25:38,209 --> 00:25:41,038
actual movie directors such as Kim Sang Ho...

740
00:25:41,039 --> 00:25:43,108
and Park Sang Ho were invited since then.

741
00:25:43,109 --> 00:25:45,149
They recommended me,

742
00:25:45,309 --> 00:25:46,648
which got me to HLKZ-TV.

743
00:25:46,649 --> 00:25:48,048
All those connections...

744
00:25:48,049 --> 00:25:51,288
- led me to acting...
- Thank goodness.

745
00:25:51,289 --> 00:25:53,718
- Good energy.
- and brought me luck.

746
00:25:53,719 --> 00:25:56,288
I've never once forgotten about that teacher.

747
00:25:56,289 --> 00:25:58,759
On Young Ok's YouTube channel,

748
00:25:58,929 --> 00:26:01,029
she met the daughter-in-law of the Korean language teacher.

749
00:26:01,099 --> 00:26:02,558
(A few months ago during a restaurant shoot)

750
00:26:02,559 --> 00:26:03,828
(Shooting with the Seoul Mother of "Culinary Class Wars 2" episode)

751
00:26:03,829 --> 00:26:06,028
- My father-in-law was a teacher...
- Yes?

752
00:26:06,029 --> 00:26:07,798
at Gyeseong Girls' High School.

753
00:26:07,799 --> 00:26:10,239
- What's his name?
- Kim Sang Jun.

754
00:26:11,269 --> 00:26:13,278
(Young Ok heard word of her Korean language teacher by chance.)

755
00:26:13,279 --> 00:26:14,508
I'm getting goosebumps.

756
00:26:14,509 --> 00:26:16,479
He's a 99-year-old grandfather right now.

757
00:26:16,509 --> 00:26:17,878
- Is he still alive?
- Yes.

758
00:26:17,879 --> 00:26:19,249
- Did he not pass away?
- No, he didn't.

759
00:26:19,379 --> 00:26:20,879
- Mr. Kim is alive?
- Yes.

760
00:26:21,149 --> 00:26:22,779
What was your student's name?

761
00:26:22,849 --> 00:26:24,019
Kim Young Ok.

762
00:26:24,949 --> 00:26:27,819
(Finally reunited with her teacher)

763
00:26:27,989 --> 00:26:30,288
(I dearly hope we meet again.)

764
00:26:30,289 --> 00:26:32,029
(Delivered a handwritten letter)

765
00:26:32,129 --> 00:26:35,729
(Please be well.)

766
00:26:39,899 --> 00:26:41,298
I had no idea he was alive.

767
00:26:41,299 --> 00:26:42,769
I heard he had passed away.

768
00:26:42,799 --> 00:26:44,608
There were many twists and turns.

769
00:26:44,609 --> 00:26:46,338
I've always wanted to give him a visit.

770
00:26:46,339 --> 00:26:47,608
- But by chance, - Really.

771
00:26:47,609 --> 00:26:49,339
- a miracle happened.
- For real.

772
00:26:49,379 --> 00:26:51,778
- The teacher...
- He was at least...

773
00:26:51,779 --> 00:26:53,678
ten years older than me.

774
00:26:53,679 --> 00:26:54,718
I met him...

775
00:26:54,719 --> 00:26:55,749
- when he was 100 years old.
- Right.

776
00:26:56,319 --> 00:26:57,518
- Actually...
- Those who know you...

777
00:26:57,519 --> 00:26:58,749
live a long life.

778
00:27:00,589 --> 00:27:02,559
You will live a long life. So will you.

779
00:27:02,719 --> 00:27:04,388
Everyone will live a long life.

780
00:27:04,389 --> 00:27:05,589
(Spreading longevity energy)

781
00:27:05,759 --> 00:27:07,558
The three wrote about their debut earlier.

782
00:27:07,559 --> 00:27:09,828
And they wrote something in the life column.

783
00:27:09,829 --> 00:27:11,298
"Major work" was what they wrote.

784
00:27:11,299 --> 00:27:13,498
- But you were in many major works.
- Exactly.

785
00:27:13,499 --> 00:27:14,938
- We can't even count them.
- Right?

786
00:27:14,939 --> 00:27:17,839
I can't really just choose one.

787
00:27:18,039 --> 00:27:19,808
But there was a work titled "Yesterday's Green Grass."

788
00:27:19,809 --> 00:27:21,938
- Wasn't it with Lee Nak Hoon?
- Yes.

789
00:27:21,939 --> 00:27:24,978
Lee Nak Hoon was my husband and an English teacher.

790
00:27:24,979 --> 00:27:26,108
- The son was Hong Yo Seop.
- Yes.

791
00:27:26,109 --> 00:27:28,378
- It was quite...
- How do you remember all that?

792
00:27:28,379 --> 00:27:29,878
a different role for me.

793
00:27:29,879 --> 00:27:31,288
I had always played...

794
00:27:31,289 --> 00:27:33,989
mischievous roles with strong personalities.

795
00:27:34,259 --> 00:27:36,988
But this role was that of a poor mother...

796
00:27:36,989 --> 00:27:39,588
who went through hardships with her children...

797
00:27:39,589 --> 00:27:42,129
and even suffered from Alzheimer's later on.

798
00:27:42,259 --> 00:27:43,628
I was grateful that...

799
00:27:43,629 --> 00:27:47,369
the others acknowledged the new side of my acting.

800
00:27:47,539 --> 00:27:48,698
There were plenty more.

801
00:27:48,699 --> 00:27:52,438
But the work where I could really show all my potential was...

802
00:27:52,439 --> 00:27:53,739
"Old Miss Diary."

803
00:27:54,009 --> 00:27:55,908
- "Old Miss Diary."
- "Old Miss Diary."

804
00:27:55,909 --> 00:27:58,748
- It was a variety show.
- Director Kim Seok Yoon.

805
00:27:58,749 --> 00:28:00,278
Setting aside the good chemistry with the director,

806
00:28:00,279 --> 00:28:02,679
I was able to express my whole self...

807
00:28:02,979 --> 00:28:04,488
in the work.

808
00:28:04,489 --> 00:28:06,488
- That's how I remember it.
- I see.

809
00:28:06,489 --> 00:28:08,218
- Mi Ja...
- I was in countless works,

810
00:28:08,219 --> 00:28:09,358
including Noh Hee Kyung's works.

811
00:28:09,359 --> 00:28:11,658
One of Noh Hee Kyung's works is...

812
00:28:11,659 --> 00:28:12,828
"Reason I Live for."

813
00:28:12,829 --> 00:28:14,098
Na Moon Hee was my younger sister...

814
00:28:14,099 --> 00:28:15,129
When will she stop?

815
00:28:16,559 --> 00:28:18,768
What's Mi Ja's major work?

816
00:28:18,769 --> 00:28:21,369
It's hard to count all of them. However,

817
00:28:21,499 --> 00:28:23,198
it would be "See and See Again."

818
00:28:23,199 --> 00:28:25,368
"See and See Again." It was such a fun drama.

819
00:28:25,369 --> 00:28:27,678
- "What is Love."
- "What is Love."

820
00:28:27,679 --> 00:28:30,708
When shooting for "What is Love,"

821
00:28:30,709 --> 00:28:32,479
I went to China.

822
00:28:32,579 --> 00:28:34,119
When passing by,

823
00:28:34,319 --> 00:28:37,188
people came out...

824
00:28:37,189 --> 00:28:39,188
and said things to me.

825
00:28:39,189 --> 00:28:42,889
I thought, "Maybe I shouldn't be here. What do I do?"

826
00:28:43,119 --> 00:28:48,059
They kept saying, "Aiqing shi shenme?"

827
00:28:48,159 --> 00:28:49,958
It meant "What is Love."

828
00:28:49,959 --> 00:28:51,398
- "What is Love."
- Yes.

829
00:28:51,399 --> 00:28:53,739
They were saying I was the actress in that drama.

830
00:28:54,169 --> 00:28:55,568
Mi Ja is the first-ever...

831
00:28:55,569 --> 00:28:57,168
- Korean wave star.
- Totally.

832
00:28:57,169 --> 00:28:58,869
- You're right.
- I'm right?

833
00:28:59,209 --> 00:29:01,438
That was when I thought I should learn Chinese.

834
00:29:01,439 --> 00:29:03,878
Only when I learned Chinese could I at least have...

835
00:29:03,879 --> 00:29:06,408
- small talks with these people.
- Communicate.

836
00:29:06,409 --> 00:29:07,548
Ni chi fan le ma?

837
00:29:07,549 --> 00:29:08,778
- Ni chi fan le ma?
- Wo...

838
00:29:08,779 --> 00:29:10,819
The Foul Mouth Grandma.

839
00:29:11,189 --> 00:29:12,318
That's not how you say it.

840
00:29:12,319 --> 00:29:14,188
Ni chi fan le ma?

841
00:29:14,189 --> 00:29:16,489
- It's the same thing. Really.
- Ni chi fan le ma?

842
00:29:16,519 --> 00:29:18,728
By the way, the drama "Fetters of Love."

843
00:29:18,729 --> 00:29:19,729
"Fetters of Love."

844
00:29:19,730 --> 00:29:21,758
Back then, this was trending in my town.

845
00:29:21,759 --> 00:29:22,859
- What was it?
- Here it is.

846
00:29:23,259 --> 00:29:25,429
"What's wrong with you?" Noh Joo Hyun.

847
00:29:25,969 --> 00:29:27,098
"Aren't you full of yourself?"

848
00:29:27,099 --> 00:29:28,198
- Go Doo Shim.
- Go Doo Shim.

849
00:29:28,199 --> 00:29:30,369
"Just put up with it." Sa Mi Ja.

850
00:29:30,769 --> 00:29:33,208
- It was like buzzwords.
- I remember.

851
00:29:33,209 --> 00:29:36,708
I appreciate that you remember them instead of me.

852
00:29:36,709 --> 00:29:38,709
- She appreciates it.
- Those things.

853
00:29:38,909 --> 00:29:42,449
All that acting made me oblivious to getting old.

854
00:29:42,919 --> 00:29:45,919
What major works of Neung Mi...

855
00:29:46,089 --> 00:29:47,318
would people know?

856
00:29:47,319 --> 00:29:50,058
- "Love and Ambition."
- "Love and Ambition."

857
00:29:50,059 --> 00:29:51,488
There are many. There's "Our Sunny Days of Youth."

858
00:29:51,489 --> 00:29:53,458
- "Our Sunny Days of Youth."
- "Our Sunny Days of Youth."

859
00:29:53,459 --> 00:29:55,598
If you think about Neung Mi's works...

860
00:29:55,599 --> 00:29:57,198
"Love and Ambition" reached 75 percent.

861
00:29:57,199 --> 00:29:58,598
- They're on another level.
- The TV ratings were 75 percent.

862
00:29:58,599 --> 00:30:00,368
"Our Sunny Days of Youth" reached 62 percent.

863
00:30:00,369 --> 00:30:01,438
("Our Sunny Days of Youth" reached 62 percent.)

864
00:30:01,439 --> 00:30:02,769
"The Moon of Seoul."

865
00:30:03,839 --> 00:30:07,408
(I think I should go back after all)

866
00:30:07,409 --> 00:30:10,209
(Even the soundtrack of this drama is iconic...)

867
00:30:10,349 --> 00:30:12,279
The ratings were 48 percent. So,

868
00:30:13,009 --> 00:30:14,678
every drama she appeared in...

869
00:30:14,679 --> 00:30:16,048
- They were a hit.
- became a hit.

870
00:30:16,049 --> 00:30:18,148
Do you have a secret of picking great dramas?

871
00:30:18,149 --> 00:30:19,788
I don't have a secret tip.

872
00:30:19,789 --> 00:30:22,018
I cared more about the role than the drama itself.

873
00:30:22,019 --> 00:30:23,189
- The role.
- Why?

874
00:30:23,589 --> 00:30:25,328
If I play a comedic role,

875
00:30:25,329 --> 00:30:27,198
then I need to switch things up next time.

876
00:30:27,199 --> 00:30:28,999
That image sticks for some years.

877
00:30:29,329 --> 00:30:31,398
If I play a gentle housewife,

878
00:30:31,399 --> 00:30:32,829
that image sticks with me for years.

879
00:30:33,099 --> 00:30:35,398
So when I get offered the same kind of role again,

880
00:30:35,399 --> 00:30:37,909
I really have no choice but to turn it down.

881
00:30:38,309 --> 00:30:41,109
"I won't do it." "I won't take this role."

882
00:30:41,439 --> 00:30:43,208
Since I turned them down like that a number of times,

883
00:30:43,209 --> 00:30:46,108
people called me Won't-do-it Nam Neung Mi.

884
00:30:46,109 --> 00:30:47,548
- Like a nickname?
- Your nickname was Won't-do-it.

885
00:30:47,549 --> 00:30:48,978
- "I won't do it."
- I wanted to do it.

886
00:30:48,979 --> 00:30:52,448
There are many dramas I missed out on like that.

887
00:30:52,449 --> 00:30:53,818
Among those...

888
00:30:53,819 --> 00:30:55,658
I'm talking about this for the first time on Men on a Mission.

889
00:30:55,659 --> 00:30:57,088
- For the first time.
- A drama you missed out on.

890
00:30:57,089 --> 00:30:58,258
- You know "Country Diaries," right?
- I do.

891
00:30:58,259 --> 00:30:59,388
(The longest-running drama, "Country Diaries")

892
00:30:59,389 --> 00:31:00,828
The role of Mama Il Yong in "Country Diaries..."

893
00:31:00,829 --> 00:31:01,898
was originally offered to me first.

894
00:31:01,899 --> 00:31:02,899
What?

895
00:31:02,900 --> 00:31:04,468
- That's right.
- She always said, "Il Yong!"

896
00:31:04,469 --> 00:31:06,199
- Kim Soo Mi...
- Why did I turn it down?

897
00:31:06,629 --> 00:31:10,038
I was playing those kinds of roles in daily and weekend dramas.

898
00:31:10,039 --> 00:31:11,668
That's why I turned it down.

899
00:31:11,669 --> 00:31:13,338
- What a shame.
- Later...

900
00:31:13,339 --> 00:31:14,778
- What a shame.
- What a shame.

901
00:31:14,779 --> 00:31:16,278
- What a shame.
- What a shame.

902
00:31:16,279 --> 00:31:18,148
- I missed many dramas like that.
- Really?

903
00:31:18,149 --> 00:31:19,908
- What a shame.
- What a shame.

904
00:31:19,909 --> 00:31:21,848
- Did you regret it later on?
- She surely respects that.

905
00:31:21,849 --> 00:31:22,918
I didn't regret it.

906
00:31:22,919 --> 00:31:24,618
I worked on "Love on a Jujube Tree" soon after.

907
00:31:24,619 --> 00:31:26,788
- That's right.
- "Love on a Jujube Tree."

908
00:31:26,789 --> 00:31:29,118
- That's right.
- "Love on a Jujube Tree."

909
00:31:29,119 --> 00:31:31,628
- That's right.
- I watched it every day.

910
00:31:31,629 --> 00:31:35,098
- That's right.
- I've noticed...

911
00:31:35,099 --> 00:31:37,098
their acting careers add up...

912
00:31:37,099 --> 00:31:38,628
- to 190 years.
- It's 190 years.

913
00:31:38,629 --> 00:31:41,999
I heard they received a huge number of awards.

914
00:31:42,399 --> 00:31:44,568
To list the major ones,

915
00:31:44,569 --> 00:31:47,078
Young Ok, in 1979,

916
00:31:47,079 --> 00:31:50,108
won the Grand Award at the Baeksang Arts Awards.

917
00:31:50,109 --> 00:31:53,548
Mi Ja, in 1970, won the Grand Award...

918
00:31:53,549 --> 00:31:54,978
- at the TBC Drama Awards.
- The Grand Award.

919
00:31:54,979 --> 00:31:56,418
- In 1970.
- Neung Mi,

920
00:31:56,419 --> 00:31:59,188
in 1977 and 1987,

921
00:31:59,189 --> 00:32:01,359
won the Excellence Award at the MBC Drama Awards.

922
00:32:02,289 --> 00:32:05,988
They've been active for 60 to 70 years.

923
00:32:05,989 --> 00:32:07,758
They would have won so many awards...

924
00:32:07,759 --> 00:32:09,558
that they probably can’t even remember them all.

925
00:32:09,559 --> 00:32:10,628
It's really amazing.

926
00:32:10,629 --> 00:32:12,629
What did you do with all those trophies?

927
00:32:12,799 --> 00:32:15,468
I couldn't keep them well.

928
00:32:15,469 --> 00:32:16,908
I put them all...

929
00:32:16,909 --> 00:32:18,708
in one cabinet.

930
00:32:18,709 --> 00:32:20,708
- You kept them in a cabinet.
- But every time we moved,

931
00:32:20,709 --> 00:32:22,278
my husband picked out the ones...

932
00:32:22,279 --> 00:32:24,608
that were dented and threw them.

933
00:32:24,609 --> 00:32:27,148
So all my past disappeared...

934
00:32:27,149 --> 00:32:29,119
What is it? Why did you cough?

935
00:32:30,049 --> 00:32:33,988
- Mi Ja is bothered by Neung Mi.
- She's...

936
00:32:33,989 --> 00:32:36,858
"She took my thunder."

937
00:32:36,859 --> 00:32:38,628
I think she was just clearing her throat.

938
00:32:38,629 --> 00:32:39,828
Should I just keep going?

939
00:32:39,829 --> 00:32:41,798
- No...
- It's because I have a cough.

940
00:32:41,799 --> 00:32:42,799
Is that so?

941
00:32:43,829 --> 00:32:45,968
I had bad luck whenever I won awards,

942
00:32:45,969 --> 00:32:47,438
so I don't like receiving awards.

943
00:32:47,439 --> 00:32:49,038
I always had bad luck after getting awards.

944
00:32:49,039 --> 00:32:50,408
After you receive awards?

945
00:32:50,409 --> 00:32:51,468
After receiving an award?

946
00:32:51,469 --> 00:32:52,608
- That's a jynx.
- But...

947
00:32:52,609 --> 00:32:53,738
after getting an award,

948
00:32:53,739 --> 00:32:55,178
didn't your pay...

949
00:32:55,179 --> 00:32:56,538
- Right.
- or status rise?

950
00:32:56,539 --> 00:32:57,949
- No.
- About that...

951
00:32:58,309 --> 00:33:00,718
There wasn't much change.

952
00:33:00,719 --> 00:33:03,348
Let me just say this.

953
00:33:03,349 --> 00:33:05,189
My pay was so low,

954
00:33:05,689 --> 00:33:07,918
so I went to see the person in charge.

955
00:33:07,919 --> 00:33:10,218
I said, "Could you raise my pay?"

956
00:33:10,219 --> 00:33:11,529
How much do you want?

957
00:33:12,289 --> 00:33:15,459
"I heard Lee Soon Jae gets paid the most. So..."

958
00:33:16,499 --> 00:33:18,398
"How can we pay you the same as someone who graduated..."

959
00:33:18,399 --> 00:33:20,338
"from Seoul National University?"

960
00:33:20,339 --> 00:33:22,498
- In those days...
- In those days...

961
00:33:22,499 --> 00:33:23,839
That happened.

962
00:33:24,509 --> 00:33:27,108
So I started tearing up,

963
00:33:27,109 --> 00:33:28,708
and I thought, "It's not going to happen."

964
00:33:28,709 --> 00:33:30,278
- So I said goodbye and walked out.
- Goodness.

965
00:33:30,279 --> 00:33:32,108
I still remember those words.

966
00:33:32,109 --> 00:33:33,778
It would remain as a lasting pain. In your heart.

967
00:33:33,779 --> 00:33:35,478
So I studied so much...

968
00:33:35,479 --> 00:33:39,118
that it was almost ridiculous.

969
00:33:39,119 --> 00:33:41,158
I studied Chinese for three years.

970
00:33:41,159 --> 00:33:44,489
I also spent many years to study English.

971
00:33:44,929 --> 00:33:47,798
Can you have a casual conversation with Yeong Cheol?

972
00:33:47,799 --> 00:33:49,228
- I can.
- Really?

973
00:33:49,229 --> 00:33:50,428
- Yeong Cheol, why don't you...
- Go on.

974
00:33:50,429 --> 00:33:51,968
Don’t ask me things like how old I am.

975
00:33:51,969 --> 00:33:53,028
"Things like how old I am."

976
00:33:53,029 --> 00:33:54,039
Except that one.

977
00:33:54,839 --> 00:33:57,938
What do you do in your free time?

